If a Character Card is defeated:
All Equipment Cards equipped on the Character Card are destroyed;
All Status(es) (not including Combat Statuses) that belong to the Character do not activate, even if they are supposed to activate;
If the defeated Character Card is supposed to be the Active Character of a player after the action that makes it defeated, that player may then select another Character Card on their side to be the Active Character, even if it is not that player's turn or if it is not in the Action Phase.
The only exception is if the defeated Character Card is the final Character Card of that player, in which case that player loses the game, and the game ends.
If a defeated Character Card later gets revived by certain effects, it will start fresh at 0 HP (plus any HP it receives at the point of revival) and 0 Energy (or equivalent), without any of the Equipment cards or Status(es) that were attached to it previously.
